title: US to cut airline traffic by 10% due to shutdown, Trump transport chief says
summary: Sean Duffy announced that cuts at 40 air traffic control locations will begin Friday if a resolution is not reached to alleviate stress on controllers. The measures aim to address ongoing concerns about controller workload and safety. Urgent discussions are underway to find alternatives before the cuts take effect.

title: Ukraine war briefing: Bulgaria moves to seize Russian refinery while Poland seeks to be US gas conduit
summary: Lukoil's Burgas plant is Bulgaria's sole refinery, underscoring the country's reliance on this facility. Meanwhile, Slovakia is increasingly finding alternatives to Russian gas as a deal for US imports develops. This situation continues to evolve as the energy landscape changes.

title: Prosecutors asked if manslaughter charge will be considered if Greg Lynn overturns high country murder conviction
summary: Appeal judges are seeking guidance on whether the motive of a former Jetstar pilot should be considered during a potential retrial for the death of Carol Clay. This inquiry may impact the legal proceedings surrounding the case. The decision could have significant implications for the prosecution's strategy.
